              <h2>Why a Digital Style Guide?</h2>
              <p>Brand, creative and content guidelines are absolutely essential to large organizations such ours. Consistency and brand messaging can suffer if guidelines aren’t in place. Especially in the digital space, content development is a team-wide effort and must be supported by the right tools and understanding. Our digital audience has unique expectations that shape every piece of content we create. Most importantly, a Digital Style Guide will:</p>

              <ol>
                <li>
                  <strong>Put our Audiences First.</strong>
                  <p>Staying in touch with visitor behaviors and activities dictates the language, mediums, and messages we use. Guidelines recognize a link between what our audience needs and the best way to fulfill that need in the most effective way.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Breed Consistency.</strong>
                  <p>Giving our audience a consistent experience builds loyalty and trust. Guidelines can be a central reference to keep the overall voice/tone consistent, and to ensure creative output reflects the quality of the written content.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Create Better Content.</strong>
                  <p>A Digital Style Guide is both a practical resource as well as a commitment to well-considered content. Personality, trends, brand values, key messaging, tone, style, image selection and formatting all contribute to the quality of our content – and guidelines keep this all in check.</p>
                </li>
              </ol>

            </div>
